********>Bugfix 1:
Author:  Scott Brozell
Date:  Dec 29, 2010

Program:  amberize_complex

Description:  the .amber.pdb, .inpcrd, and .prmtop Amber score input
filenames for neutralized and neutralized-solvated RNA complexes are
missing the ligand name.  Thus, these filenames are incorrect because
they duplicate the corresponding receptor only filenames.

Fix:  make the following changes to the file src/accessories/amberize_complex
and reinstall that script: cd src/accessories;
patch -c amberize_complex bugfix.1; make install
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** amberize_complex	16 Oct 2009 19:50:22 -0000	1.16
--- amberize_complex	30 Dec 2010 00:42:17 -0000
***************
*** 118,129 ****
  output_pdb=$receptor_name.$ligand_name.amber.pdb
  output_prmtop=$receptor_name.$ligand_name.prmtop
  receptor_pdb_file_prefix=$receptor_name
! outputna_inpcrd=$receptor_pdb_file_prefix.na.inpcrd
! outputna_pdb=$receptor_pdb_file_prefix.na.amber.pdb
! outputna_prmtop=$receptor_pdb_file_prefix.na.prmtop
! outputnah2o_inpcrd=$receptor_pdb_file_prefix.na.h2o.inpcrd
! outputnah2o_pdb=$receptor_pdb_file_prefix.na.h2o.amber.pdb
! outputnah2o_prmtop=$receptor_pdb_file_prefix.na.h2o.prmtop
  
  if [ ! -f "$input_pdb" ]
  then
